    <h1>Palette</h1>
    <p>Where the base colors are defined for BaseWeb. These colors are used throughout the framework and can be overridden to preference. To make them easiest to remember, every color is defined using the base color then modifier.</p>
    <p>In the case of a mixed color, the primary (red, yellow, blue) color is always used first and the secondary (orange, green, violet) after:</p>
    
    <pre><code>$[color]-[modifier]
$blue-light

$[primary]-[secondary]-[modifier]
$yellow-green-lighter</code></pre>
    
    <p>All the shade variations (light, lighter, dark, darker) are created using the base primary and secondary colors and are modified using these degree variables:</p>
    
    <ul class="variables">
      
      <li><code>$light-deg</code> <code class="value">5%</code></li>
      <li><code>$lighter-deg</code> <code class="value">10%</code></li>
      <li><code>$dark-deg</code> <code class="value">5%</code></li>
      <li><code>$darker-deg</code> <code class="value">10%</code></li>
    
    </ul>
    
